1. Upload the Code
Disconnect the HC-05 module from the Arduino before uploading (or remove TX/RX wires).
Upload the sketch.
After uploading, reconnect the HC-05.
2. Wiring
HC-05	Arduino Uno
VCC	5V
GND	GND
TXD	RX (D0)
RXD	TX (D1) (preferably through a voltage divider)

LED connections:

Red LED → D2
Green LED → D3
Blue LED → D4
Each LED should have a 220Ω resistor.
3. Pair the Phone
Turn on the Arduino.
HC-05 LED should blink rapidly.
On your Android phone:
Open Settings → Bluetooth
Turn Bluetooth ON.
Search for devices.
Select HC-05 (or HC-06 if that's the module name).
Enter the pairing PIN:
1234
If that doesn't work, try 0000.
After pairing, the HC-05 LED will still blink until an app connects.
4. Install a Bluetooth Terminal App

Examples:

Serial Bluetooth Terminal
Bluetooth Terminal HC-05
5. Connect to HC-05
Open the Bluetooth Terminal app.
Tap Connect.
Select HC-05.
Once connected, the HC-05 LED will blink slowly (about once every 2 seconds), indicating a successful connection.
6. Send These Commands

Send uppercase letters:

Send	Result
R	Red LED ON
G	Green LED ON
B	Blue LED ON
X	All LEDs OFF
F	Flash all LEDs 5 times

Any other character will display:

Invalid Command!
7. Expected Serial Monitor Output

When the Arduino starts:

===== Bluetooth LED Controller =====
Commands:
R - Red LED ON
G - Green LED ON
B - Blue LED ON
X - All LEDs OFF
F - Flash LEDs 5 Times
-----------------------------------

After sending commands:

R
Red LED ON

G
Green LED ON

B
Blue LED ON

F
Flashing LEDs...
Done

X
All LEDs OFF
